race.comment: WILDSPITZE (4) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome two back but go on the solid placing at the Gold Coast last time out. Gets 1.5kg weight relief with the claim and this is not an overly strong affair. The one to beat. WHATA SORT (6) is ready to peak now fourth-up from the break and gets the services of Thornton in the irons. Can improve sharply. QUARTZOPOLIS (1) hit the frame at Warwick on debut and will have derived a stack of benefit from that race day experience. In the mix. FAR CRY (7) will be better for that first-up hit-out and may earn some minor money. PARADISE AS USUAL (8) next in line from the inside alley.
